snippet: Victoria Azarenka, the top-ranked women’s player, fell Sunday to Dominika Cibulkova, who had twice been on the verge of knocking out Azarenka’s defenses in the past two years.
abstract: Dominika Cibulkova defeats top-ranked Victoria Azarenka in the fourth round of the French Open tennis tournament.
lead_paragraph: Victoria Azarenka, the top-ranked women’s player, fell Sunday to Dominika Cibulkova, who had twice been on the verge of knocking out Azarenka’s defenses in the past two years.

headline.seo: 2012 French Open: Azarenka Ousted in 4th Round
headline.main: Cooler Weather Brings Trouble for Top Players at French Open
headline.print_headline: One Top-Seeded Player Falls; Another Makes Escape in Paris
